nfc-eventd
------------------------------------------
Nfc-eventd is a NFC monitor daemon which is able to launch modules (libraries)
on action (tag inserted or removed)

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.34-6
  libdbus-glib_1_2-0.102-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.42.1-2
  libnfc5-1.7.1-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-2
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://code.google.com/p/nfc-tools/

Canonical download:
  https://nfc-tools.googlecode.com/files/nfc-eventd-0.1.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack nfc-eventd-0.1.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./nfc-eventd-0.1.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/nfc-eventd-0.1.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/nfc-eventd-0.1.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(nfc-eventd)
  /etc/dbus-1/system.d/nfc-eventd-dbus.conf
  /etc/nfc-eventd.conf
  /usr/bin/nfc-eventd.exe
  /usr/lib/nfc-eventd/modules/nem_dbus.dll
  /usr/lib/nfc-eventd/modules/nem_execute.dll
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/nfc-eventd.README
  /usr/share/doc/nfc-eventd/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/nfc-eventd/COPYING

------------------

